               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18380402-name-526" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18380402-name-526" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380402-name-526" type="surname" value="JENNINGS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380402-name-526" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS JENNINGS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am potman to George Caslake, at the Boston Arms, Preston-street, Regent's-park. On the morning of the 24th of March, I saw the prisoner with a bag—I followed him up Park-terrace—he ran as soon as he saw me, and I after him—he dropped the bag—I caught him—he said, "Don't give me in charge, if you please "—I gave him to the policeman, brought him back, picked up the bag and the pots in it, which belonged to my master.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi>, As I went up Preston-street, a young man put a bag in to my hand, and said, "Here, young man, here is something for you"—I heart a cry of "Stop thief"—I immediately ran after him, and the young man caught me—I said, "Are you going to blame me for it?" <hi rend="italic">Witness</hi>. He said nothing about another man—he owned the bag, and said they were the first pots he had ever stolen.</p>
